# Changelog

## [1.1.4] - 2026-05-18

### Fixed
- Fixing target handling for pointerenter event handler that could throw js error.

## [1.1.3] - 2026-05-14

### Fixed
- Fixed `keydown` handler accumulation in `carousel-lightbox.js`: each lightbox open previously attached a new listener without reliably removing the previous one (due to new function reference per call), causing stacked handlers across multiple open/close cycles. Now uses a module-level `activeKeyHandler` reference cleaned up in `close()`.
- Removed broken `keydown` handler in `frontend.js` that referenced undefined `showNext()`, `showPrev()`, and `closeLightbox()` functions, which would throw a `ReferenceError` whenever the WP native lightbox was open and a key was pressed.
- Fixed `carousel-lightbox.js` asset enqueue using a hardcoded `'1.0'` version string; now uses `filemtime()` for proper cache busting, consistent with other enqueued assets.
- Fixed `carousel-lightbox.css` enqueue missing a version argument; now uses `filemtime()`.
- Fixed `lazyload` cleanup loop in the footer hydration script to also set `src`/`srcset` from `data-src`/`data-srcset` on matched images, and extended the selector to include `img.lazyloading` in addition to `img.lazyload`.
- Fixed `loc-prev` and `loc-next` buttons appearing below vertical center (`top: 50%` without `transform: translateY(-50%)`).
- Fixed `z-index:3` missing space (cosmetic, now `z-index: 3`).

### Improved
- Added `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, and `aria-label="Image lightbox"` to the carousel overlay for screen reader compatibility.
- Added `aria-label="Previous image"` and `aria-label="Next image"` to prev/next navigation buttons.
- Replaced text character `x` in the close button with the proper `&#x2715;` (✕) symbol; replaced `‹`/`›` entities with their correct Unicode equivalents.
- Added `alt=""` to the lightbox `<img>` element to suppress redundant screen reader announcements.
- Added hover opacity transition to all lightbox control buttons for better visual feedback.
- Added `debounce` (50ms) to the `MutationObserver` callback in `frontend.js` to reduce excessive `querySelector` calls on busy DOM mutations.
- Touch devices now keep the close button visible; only prev/next are hidden (swipe gestures handle navigation).
- Unified all file version headers to `1.1.3`.

## [1.1.2] - 2026-05-11

### Fixed
- Fixing missing images problem for Lightbox Overlay carousel on first load.

## [1.1.1] - 2026-05-09

### Fixed
- Removing unnecessary and problematic click handler which caused conflict in WP Gallery Block instances.

## [1.1.0] - 2026-05-08

### Added
- Improved WordPress lightbox integration for Carousel Slider Block galleries.
- Added proactive image hydration for Swiper/Gutenberg carousel images before opening the lightbox overlay.
- Added support for lazy-loaded `picture`, `source`, `srcset`, and responsive image handling to use with lightbox galleries.

### Fixed
- Fixed issue where navigating the lightbox carousel could display placeholders or missing images when the main Swiper carousel had not yet loaded all lazy-loaded slides.
- Fixed synchronization issues between lazy-loaded Swiper slides and the WordPress lightbox overlay gallery.
- Improved first-open behavior of lightbox galleries by ensuring all carousel images are fetched and processed before overlay navigation becomes active.

### Improved
- Optimized interaction flow between lazy loading, Swiper carousels, and WordPress lightbox overlays.
- Reduced cases where users needed to close and reopen the lightbox to access all gallery images.


## [1.0.0] - 2026-04-24

### Initial Release
- Initial public release.
- Added Swiper-based image carousel support.
- Added WordPress/Gutenberg lightbox integration.
